%% Model Registry Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-2.19/model-registry-operator.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant IstioGW as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>80 or 443/TCP
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>(CUSTOM action)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Sidecar as Istio Sidecar<br/>mTLS ISTIO_MUTUAL
    participant REST as rest-container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant GRPC as grpc-container<br/>9090/TCP gRPC
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432 or 3306/TCP

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: REST API Request (with Istio)
    Client->>IstioGW: HTTP/HTTPS Request<br/>TLS (if configured)
    IstioGW->>Authorino: AuthorizationPolicy<br/>(CUSTOM action, mTLS)
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/TLS
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Token Valid
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(get services/{name})
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Authorized
    Authorino-->>IstioGW: Allow
    IstioGW->>Sidecar: Forward (mTLS ISTIO_MUTUAL)
    Sidecar->>REST: HTTP Request<br/>8080/TCP
    REST->>GRPC: gRPC (localhost)<br/>9090/TCP
    GRPC->>DB: DB wire protocol<br/>Configurable SSL
    DB-->>GRPC: Query Result
    GRPC-->>REST: gRPC Response
    REST-->>Sidecar: HTTP Response
    Sidecar-->>IstioGW: mTLS Response
    IstioGW-->>Client: HTTP/HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Direct REST API Request (without Istio)
    Client->>REST: HTTPS via OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP edge TLS
    Note right of Client: OCP Router terminates TLS<br/>forwards to 8080/TCP plaintext
    REST->>GRPC: gRPC (localhost)<br/>9090/TCP
    GRPC->>DB: DB wire protocol<br/>Configurable SSL
    DB-->>GRPC: Query Result
    GRPC-->>REST: gRPC Response
    REST-->>Client: HTTP Response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: ModelRegistry CR created/updated
    K8sAPI-->>REST: Watch notification<br/>HTTPS/TLS
    Note right of REST: Operator reconciler<br/>(not REST container)
    REST->>K8sAPI: CRUD: Deployments, Services,<br/>Routes, Istio resources<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
